"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5193363-2024-01-10-usa-basketball-player-pools-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NBA    PARIS - This is preposterous, to the point of non-belief, but on Wednesday a French reporter asked theBrooklyn Nets'Mikal Bridgesabout his hopes and/or intentions to play for Team USA at the Paris Olympics this summer, and he said he'd forgotten the Games were going to be here.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bridges was seated before a throng of mostly French reporters Wednesday after the Nets practiced in a Parisian suburb, ahead of their Thursday game with theCleveland Cavaliers.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  TheNBAcoming to Paris is a big deal (Thursday's tilt will be the third regular-season game in France ever), and the upcoming Paris Games, in which the biggest stars in the NBA are expected to play for their countries, is a huge ancillary topic of discussion this week.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 496, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9493221527769361, \"rank\": 0.053343324534248934, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0659773444453446e-25, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American players have been talking about Paris since the moment USA beat France in the Tokyo Olympic finals, and Bridges, a member of last summer's World Cup team that qualified the United States for the 2024 Olympics, surely had not forgotten.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 791, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9493221527769361, \"rank\": 0.053343324534248934, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999942838258, \"rank\": 4.392417636954866e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the kind of deflection a player might use to get away from a line of questioning he does not want to answer - like he knows something that is not supposed to be out there yet.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Just waiting to see - if (the invite) comes, it comes,\\\" Bridges toldThe Athletic, after the larger scrum.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think I bear my head on it too much, because I am so locked in on trying to figure out everything here (with the Nets).\\\"\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Frankly, it was a much more plausible answer, and in truth, according to Bridges and numerous league sources, Team USA has not sent any formal invites for its 12-man roster for Paris.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, those sources said, USA Basketball will begin reaching out to potential prospects before January is out, running through between 35 and 40 names on a master list of players who primarily are Olympic or World Cup vets, many (but not all of them) stars, with room potentially for a few players who perhaps do not check any of those boxes.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9682222333811579, \"rank\": 0.032820736317672086, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least a few of the names on that list, the sources said, will be players from the 2023 World Cup team that finished fourth last summer, and the list is expected to be announced in the coming days or weeks.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, USA managing director Grant Hill and coach Steve Kerr had suggested \\\"player pools\\\" would be discontinued; that, in the modern era, it was more effective for the American national team to send invites privately, rather than ask a larger group of players to try out.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1751283763131969e-26, \"text\": \"Grant Hill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Kerr\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998979637946, \"rank\": 1.0200169845813436e-07, \"text\": \"American national team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, USA Basketball pieced together the World Cup roster without a pool, and it was widely expected the same process would be followed for theOlympics.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2445, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9682222333811579, \"rank\": 0.032820736317672086, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's basketball, however, will continue using the player-pool system for 2024.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  But the interest in the 2024 Games is perhaps unprecedented, with young, upcoming stars like Bridges,Tyrese HaliburtonandAnthony Edwards, as well as aging superstars with gold medals likeLeBron JamesandKevin Durant, all hoping to play for Team USA.Steph Curry, who has two World Cup golds but has never played in the Olympics, has said he wants to play.Jayson TatumandDevin Booker, members of the Tokyo Games gold-medalist team, want to play.\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2898, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6950495277153082e-15, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So doesJoel Embiid, the reigning NBA MVP who has American and French passports and said he would play for the USA this summer.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1060372625593153e-12, \"text\": \"NBA MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Creating a pool, or master list, or larger group of \\\"finalists\\\" allows the USA staff to keep a larger number of talented, perhaps deserving players engaged rather than discouraged, after the public declarations of interest from the biggest American stars.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3336, \"end\": 3339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3501, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It allows a more natural selection process, which is majorly tied to how the NBA playoffs unfold, and who is healthy or otherwise not worn out when their season is over.\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3594, \"end\": 3597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0659773444453446e-25, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bridges was the USA's third-leading scorer at the World Cup at 13.6 ppg, behind Edwards (18.9 ppg) andAustin Reaves(13.8 ppg).\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3704, \"end\": 3707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was second on that team with 1.4 steals per game, behind only Haliburton (1.5 spg).\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3880, \"end\": 3890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyrese_Haliburton\", \"score\": 0.9923829817368044, \"rank\": 0.007674688187087964, \"text\": \"Haliburton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyrese_Haliburton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyrese_Haliburton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hill, Kerr, and Sean Ford, another high-ranking USA official greatly involved in picking the roster, will want to field a balanced team with international experience, with greater talent and depth in the frontcourt, and with at least a few players willing to take on lesser roles than they are used to in the NBA.\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 4215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3923, \"end\": 3927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"score\": 0.994928141525723, \"rank\": 0.005097344446101903, \"text\": \"Ford\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 3950, \"end\": 3953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4211, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0659773444453446e-25, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bridges toldThe Athletiche felt he'd earned a place on the USA roster this summer, but \\\"I feel like all of us (from the 2023 team) pretty much have.\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think we all have good ability.\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like everybody has a shot at it, but I would say I definitely do.\\\"\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr previously toldThe Athletiche would like to see players from last summer's team on the Paris roster, and Haliburton toldThe Athleticthat he and Edwards believe they should be considered.\", \"from\": 4475, \"to\": 4666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4567, \"end\": 4572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  In the meantime, any American on the Nets or Cavs in Paris this week even remotely associated with Team USA was bound to be asked.\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4704, \"end\": 4712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4736, \"end\": 4741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4782, \"end\": 4790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Donovan Mitchell, who played for the Americans at the 2019 FIBA World Cup, was injured for the Tokyo Games, and passed on last summer's World Cup, said: \\\"Yeah, that's the goal, to be back here this summer (with Team USA).\", \"from\": 4815, \"to\": 5036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4815, \"end\": 4831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donovan_Mitchell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donovan Mitchell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donovan_Mitchell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donovan_Mitchell\"}, {\"begin\": 5026, \"end\": 5034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the goal.\\\"\", \"from\": 5037, \"to\": 5054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo: Yong Teck Lim / Getty Images)  Spot the pattern.\", \"from\": 5056, \"to\": 5112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Connect the terms  Find the hidden link between sports terms  Play today's puzzle  Joe Vardonis a senior NBA writer for The Athletic, based in Cleveland.Follow Joe on Twitter@joevardon\", \"from\": 5113, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5196, \"end\": 5199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9998724973457682, \"rank\": 0.00011848982579625639, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 5218, \"end\": 5221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0659773444453446e-25, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 5233, \"end\": 5245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Athletic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Athletic\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Athletic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Athletic\"}, {\"begin\": 5280, \"end\": 5287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.272002796964646e-11, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}]}"